<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4359046>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 17. Micrographs of Henlea nasuta (Eisen, 1878). A. Intestinal diverticula (dv=dorsal vessel). B. Coelomocytes. C. Plurilobed middorsal and midventral projections of oesophageal appendages in IV (side view). D. Winding canal of oesophageal appendages in IV–V. E. Clitellar glands, dorsal view. F. Bursal slits and clitellar glands, ventral view. G. Sperm funnel. H. Spermathecae. All in vivo. Scale bars 50 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4359046/files/figure.png" .

